extends tutorial.pug

block title
  | F4 Framework Tutorial - Interactive Learning Guide

block content
  .chapter-header
    h1 Welcome to F4 Framework Tutorial
    p.description Learn to build modern PHP web applications with F4's lightweight, module-based architecture

  .content-section
    h2 About This Tutorial

    p This interactive tutorial will guide you through all the essential concepts of the F4 framework. Each chapter builds upon the previous one, providing hands-on examples and live demonstrations.

    h3 What You'll Learn

    ul
      li How to create routes and handle HTTP requests
      li Parameter validation using PHP attributes
      li Middleware for request/response processing
      li Building REST APIs with route groups
      li Database integration and query building
      li Multi-language support (i18n)
      li Exception handling and error pages

    .info-box
      strong Note:
      | This tutorial application is itself built using F4! You can explore the source code to see real-world examples of all the concepts we'll cover.

  .content-section
    h2 Chapters

    each $chapter in $response['data']['chapters']
      .demo-box
        h4
          span.chapter-number-badge= 'Chapter ' . (int)$chapter['number']
          = $chapter['title']
        p.chapter-description= $chapter['description']
        a.chapter-link(href=$chapter['path']) Start Chapter →

  .content-section
    h2 Prerequisites

    p Before starting this tutorial, you should have:

    ul
      li Basic knowledge of PHP (version 8.3+)
      li Understanding of HTTP and web development concepts
      li A local development environment with PHP and PostgreSQL
      li Composer installed for dependency management

  .content-section
    h2 Getting Started

    p Ready to begin? Start with Chapter 01 to learn the basics of routing and templates.

    p
      a.start-button(href="/tutorial/01-hello-world") Start Learning →
